**`from_utf8_lossy` silently corrupts data on round-trip**

If a blob value contains invalid UTF-8 (even a single byte), `from_utf8_lossy` replaces it with U+FFFD. On the next `save_sync_state`, the replacement character is written back as the new value, permanently destroying the original data with no warning. This should use `from_utf8` and either skip or error on invalid entries.